data.title: Jon Brockman Traded To Houston Rockets From Milwaukee Bucks
data.meta_description: Former Washington Husky big man Jon Brockman was traded to the Houston Rockets from the Milwaukee Bucks.
data.text:
The quest for Jon Brockman to play on every single NBA team is alive and well. His fourth season in the NBA will be spent on his third team. Brockman was dealt to the Houston Rockets as part of the trade that sent Samuel Dalembert to the Milwaukee Bucks.

Brockman originally spent his first season with the Sacramento Kings after being drafted with their second round pick, and was dealt to the Bucks in July in exchange for Darnell Jackson. Brockman has averaged about two points and three rebounds per game in his first three years in the league, mostly as a utility bench player.
